quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,37,"Verily, therein is indeed a reminder for him who has a heart or gives ear while he is heedful."
  50,38,"And indeed We created the heavens and the earth and all between them in six Days and nothing of fatigue touched Us."
  50,39,"So bear with patience (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) all that they say, and glorify the Praises of your Lord, before the rising of the sun and before (its) setting (i.e. the Fajr, Zuhr, and ‘Asr prayers){1}.",1:[{50:39}.]
  51,31,"[Ibrâhîm (Abraham)] said: "
  51,32,"They said: "
  51,33,"To send down upon them stones of baked clay."
  52,22,"And We shall provide them with fruit and meat such as they desire."
  52,23,"There they shall pass from hand to hand a (wine) cup, free from any Laghw (dirty, false, evil vain talk between them), and free from sin{1} (because it will be lawful for them to drink).",1:[{52:23} See Footnote b, c and d of {2:219}.]
  52,24,"And there will go round boy-servants of theirs, to serve them as if they were preserved pearls."
  53,16,"When that covered the lote-tree which did cover it!{1}",1:[{53:16} It is said that the Lot-Tree was covered with the light of Allah along with the angels and also with different kinds of colours. (Please see T. Ibn Kathîr).]
  53,17,"The sight (of Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) turned not aside (right or left), nor it transgressed beyond the limit (ordained for it)."
  53,18,"Indeed he (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) did see of the Greatest Signs, of his Lord (Allâh)."
  54,7,"They will come forth, with humbled eyes from (their) graves as if they were locusts spread abroad,"
  54,8,"Hastening towards the caller. The disbelievers will say: "
  54,9,"The people of Nûh (Noah) denied (their Messenger) before them. They rejected Our slave, and said: "
  55,1,"The Most Gracious (Allâh)!"
  55,2,"He has taught (you mankind) the Qur’ân (by His Mercy)."
  55,3,"He created man."